Wanting to start a fitness journey in 2023 but feel lost? These are my TOP TIPS for a successful fitness journey you can stick to:

- good form over heavy weights: this one is pretty simple…if you’re throwing weights around that are too heavy for you, you’re likely to not only end up hurt but you also just simply won’t be getting the full benefits of each lift if you’re unable to complete the full range of motion with intention (fully contracting the target muscle group)

- stop spending your $$$ on 6 week challenges: it’s not to say challenges are “bad” but they get you in the mindset that all your problems will be solved in 6 weeks & then you can get back to living your life the way you were before the challenge & lose all progress. Join something SUSTAINABLE that’s designed to help you enjoy fitness long term (like, forever). I have my program linked in my bio if you need a place to start 🫶🏼

- follow a program tailored to your goals: kind of simple…but going into the gym without a plan especially if you’re new is more than likely going to leave you lost, confused, frustrated, and anxious. Following a plan means that so much if the work has already been done for you and all you have to do is execute in order to see progress 🤌🏼

this is your sign to stop doing sit-ups hoping they will “tone” your core & pickup some Pilates core exercises instead - this move is one of my favs & how to get the most out of the his move is explained below👇🏼 

1) from a table top position (back flat to the bench) SQUEEZE the ball in between your feet

2) as you extend your feet out, try to keep your feet in the same plane (aka the same height) & do NOT let your back arch - keep that pelvis tucked with your spine glued to the ground or bench as you squeeze the ball in between your feet extending out and back in!

traditional core exercises like crunches and sit-ups do little to nothing to improve stability

core stability is a VITAL component of health, physical performance, & is essential for activities we already do daily like climbing stairs & carrying heavy loads OR KIDS 

core stability/balance is especially important to work on as young adults to reduce the risk of falls/injuries as we age 

IMPROVE your balance by doing core exercises that are functional like this one! I do 3 sets of 8 each side!

TWO THINGS YOU MUST DO TO MAKE THIS A GLUTE EXERCISE & NOT A BACK EXERCISE ⬇️

1) tuck your tailbone & squeeze your glutes at the top - it will help to have your toes pointed slightly outward when you do this but sometimes that feels awkward for me depending on the machine!

2) slightly round your back - we really want to keep from arching so that you do not engage your back (since the goal here is GLUTES)

UNILATERAL MOVEMENTS ARE LITERALLY KEY TO THE GLUTES OF YOUR DREAMS ✨ try this superset and thank me later 🍑🥵 

Also, a superset just means you do one exercise & then a different one and then ya go BACK to doing the first one and so on! For this, I’d do the first exercise (single leg hip thrusts) for 8 reps then do the other leg for the same number of reps. Then I would “superset” it with the second exercise (single leg RDL) for 8 reps on one leg & then switch to the other leg! I would then do that for a total of 3 sets!

my favorite day ever on our favorite weekend ever 🇺🇸 

every detail was intentional - from getting married on 4th of July weekend, to the linens matching my dress, to the bridesmaid dresses matching the drink tags, to our first dance song being written into our vows 💕 I loved planning this fairytale of a day & it came together more perfectly than I could have ever imagined

a moment for the details 🥂🎂🌸💍 

my original plan for everything was gold/champagne/white but when I just HAD to have the black and white dance floor, I knew I needed to tie in the black by adding some black details to the table (hence the black rim on the chargers + black napkins & thank you notes). 

I was also advised to add a TINY bit of color to the florals to and not to go plain white to give some dimension since so much of the room is white and we didn’t want the florals just getting lost in the sauce - so I asked my florist to go as neutral as possible and she definitely did just that! 

For the champagne wall, I had been told by a few people that they were “overdone” and even that the champagne gets flat so we made sure to make it unique and to use it as seating chart display and fill the glasses about 10 minutes before guests needed walk past it in order to find their seat (each glass has the guest’s name along with their table number on it). 

Another detail that was important to me, was using decor that was USA made! The neon sign one that I purchased through STL made @eyecandyconfetti & the custom acrylic drink tags are by Ten600Designs on Etsy based in FL (I placed an order on Sunday and had them by Wednesday). 

I was certainly worried that it would all chaotically clash and was STUNNED to see it all go so beautifully together 🫶🏼

current workout split ⬇️ 

Monday: unilateral legs 
Tuesday: core/pelvic floor 
Wednesday: active recovery/rest day
Thursday: full body 
Friday: active recovery/rest day
Saturday: upper body 
Sunday: active recovery/rest day

For this rest day circuit, I roll my feet for 2 min + roll my body for 2 min. Then I complete each movement you see 10 times (on each side when that applies). Tag a friend who needs to add some mobility/rest to their routine 💕

Gone are the days where I feel the need to be in the gym EVERYDAY & gone are the days when I spend more than 45 minutes training. 

This is my sweet spot, where my body feels at peace, where I’m exercising to take care of my future self versus to torture my current self. 

I try to aim for 8-10k steps a day but I don’t obsess over it. I go for walks when I feel like I’ve been sedentary for 2-3 hours and am itching to move but I don’t stress if it’s been a busy day and I didn’t have the time. 

I don’t then double my steps the next day, I simply resume movement as normal. Movement is a form of self love and we have got to be in a better habit of treating it that way as a society 💕

Maui dump + guide of our favorites 

To be honest, this was the LEAST prepared I’ve ever been for a trip in my life. We made a FEW reservations ahead of time but most of what we did was just because we decided to do that day of! 

Also note that we of course tossed and turned over whether to go due to the recent tragedy as we did not want to be insensitive, but everything we were hearing from locals was to absolutely visit so long as you are respectful! 

Things we did:
- Road to Hana (download all trails app, it’s pretty helpful in avoiding crowded hikes/gives you exact directions how to get there)
- on the drive to the road to Hana, the town you pass through (Paia) is a really good spot to shop around/have lunch! Every shop + restaurant there was worth walking into!
- Beach at Mama’s Fish House (lots of 🐢 watching)
- Black Sand Beach (make a res, we were only able to drive by)
- Snorkeling (we aren’t super adventurous/didn’t want to risk shark encounter lol so we only did this super close to shore)

Places we ate:
- dinner at Morimoto (Andaz)
- Luau at Andaz (WORTH it to splurge on the more expensive tix so you’re not at a table w strangers)
- dinner at Duo (four seasons)
- dinner at Restaurant @ Hotel Wailea 

Where we stayed 
@waileabeachresort saved our honeymoon because got absolutely catfished by an Airbnb which was of course a stressful way to start the trip but we THOROUGHLY enjoyed where we ended up staying! 

This is of course a short list, so if you have been and have suggestions, add them to the comments below!

Acupuncture is a science backed and effective method for encouraging your body’s ability to heal. 

Western culture often doubts the credibility of acupuncture, but the truth is, acupuncture changes your body’s stress response overtime. Heart rate variability reports give a detailed and quantified look at stress levels before, during, and after treatment. 

Recent science validates that your body is actually like an interconnected web. Heal the web in one area, and the whole body benefits from decreased information, boosted, neurochemicals, and improved health!

12 DAYS OF WELL-MAS ✨🎄❄️day 3: red light therapy 

Truly the best investment I ever made for my skin was a red light therapy device.
 
It can help rejuvenate the skin, create smoothness, elasticity, and just overall improve the appearance of your skin. It does this by helping to build collagen &  it reduces the enzyme that breaks down collagen. 

Red light therapy can also promote healthy tissue by increasing the production of ATP so our cells are therefore producing more energy (which is why it can help with tissue maintenance and repair). 

The PROBLEM is that red light therapy devices are not really standardized so it’s hard to know which ones are better than others. The devices used in offices and spas are STRONGER which is why I bought a device used at a few med-spas I have visited! 

This is NOT SPONSORED in any way shape or form & I paid for my device almost 4 years ago and absolutely love it. I have a @celluma_led_therapy pro device which means mine has 3 settings: red, infrared, and blue light!

my husband & I booked ourselves the “Camellia” treatment! essentially, hair follicles on the scalp can get clogged with a variety of substances…the most common being sebum (your natural oil that is secreted from the sebaceous gland in the hair follicle). 

the exfoliation and massage portions of this scalp treatment help to stimulate blood flow to your scalp, making it easier for blood to reach your follicles and deliver important nutrients. the hair that grows out of those nutrient-rich follicles will be much healthier

if you don’t have one of these near you, you can massage your own scalp at home using your fingernails & a good scalp oil! my favorite is by @lookorganics 

it’s so new that there’s not even a location to tag on IG but it is called H2O House Chicago & if you need the link to book it just comment below “link” and I’ll send it to you!

this year’s theme: resilience ❤️ I suppose as humans, we have “no choice” but to get back up when life knocks us down…but I feel like we actually have a choice between two options:

1) life knocks us down & so we develop a chip on our shoulder and adopt phrases like “ugh it’s always something” & “when am I going to catch a break?”
2) life knocks us down, we process those emotions and let ourselves feel, then we get up and use those experiences to make us stronger and more RESILIENT ❤️ 

life can make us more empathetic, loving, wise, & resilient or it can make us spiteful, angry, and unkind all depending on how you choose to show up after being knocked down

choose resilience with me this year, no matter how many times you feel like you have been “knocked down”
